,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Prepare a 1x working solution of TE<\/span><span> using 20x TE (supplied) and sterile di H<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>O. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871246,"guid":"9FACFE003B9211EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","previous_id":871245,"previous_guid":"8F56DD003B9211EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EA616FD4D2674489A35D44998215F71B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Sample Prep + Standard Curve"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"21B4C6116BC3499097BE8D83FD9F3558","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Prepare a working solution of PicoGreen<\/span><span> by doing a 1:200 dilution (PicoGreen: final volume). Prepare solution in plastic falcon tube wrapped in aluminum foil, as the reagent is light sensitive. Do not use glass as PicoGreen may adsorb to glass.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;\">You need 48ul of total solution per sample. Make extra for errors.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871247,"guid":"A8F517403B9211EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","previous_id":871246,"previous_guid":"9FACFE003B9211EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E7677523991640BBA40958ED7860F236","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Sample Prep + Standard Curve"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F43571A61B5546D19DE7DC7387EA6A88","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Prepare standard curve<\/span><span> using Lambda DNA standard (supplied at a concentration of 100ng\/ul or 100ug\/ml, comes with PicoGreen) and 1x TE in 8 tubes, as below. Load 2ul from each tube into one column (A12-H12). <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">You will need to increase these volumes if running >2 plates.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Tube #<\/span><span>                <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Contents<\/span><span>                                 <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Concentration<\/span><span>        <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Final volume<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">1               10 ul TE;  10 ul Lambda DNA            50.0 ng\/ul                 10 ul<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2              10 ul TE;   10 ul from tube                 125.0 ng\/ul                10 ul<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">3              10 ul TE;   10 ul from tube                 212.5 ng\/ul                8 ul<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">4              4 ul TE;      6 ul from tube                   37.5 ng\/ul                 10 ul<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">5              6 ul TE;      4 ul from tube                   35.0 ng\/ul                  9 ul<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">6              8 ul TE;      2 ul from tube                 32.5 ng\/ul                  10 ul<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">7              4 ul TE;      1 ul from tube                 51.0 ng\/ul                    5 ul<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">8              10 ul TE                                                    0.0 ng\/ul               10 ul<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871248,"guid":"44B204903B9311EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","previous_id":871247,"previous_guid":"A8F517403B9211EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"9B9B8E1A1B0A40AFAEE310031110C360","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Sample Prep + Standard Curve"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BED7E354A9F04BCDB485C9791A6CEA38","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Pipet <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">2ul sample into wells in Costar black microplate<\/span><span> (#3915), with the standard curve in wells A1-H1. Use one column of wells for a standard curve in each plate. Pipet your samples into the center of each well. If your DNA is in tubes, this process will take a long time, and you risk dehydration of the samples. You will need to work quickly, and cover or seal plates somehow after finishing one. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871249,"guid":"4DDD6E103B9311EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","previous_id":871248,"previous_guid":"44B204903B9311EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B2A27962BD1A4CF5AC097961F7005873","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Sample Prep + Standard Curve"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C5609234B1AF480EAC4CBD1B45BC50DF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">THE REMAINING STEPS SHOULD DONE BY A PLATE READER- You will need:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Reservoir and PicoGreen working solution<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">P200 multichannel pipet<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">As many tips as you have plates\/samples<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Waste container<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">USB drive<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Samples in Costar plates (stack and use lid for top one)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Aluminum foil covers + piece of aluminum foil<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Protocol<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Writing utensil<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Gloves<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871251,"guid":"6CD793403B9311EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","previous_id":871249,"previous_guid":"4DDD6E103B9311EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2602603DB7604385BBF0F3EB08E35696","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Plate Reader"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"1846CAF7DF5145AC9390E4C9CF412E1F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Pour PicoGreen solution into reservoir and <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">pipet 48 ul PicoGreen working solution into each well<\/span><span>. Cover plate with aluminum foil covered Rainin lid. Cover reservoir with aluminum foil. Tip plate slightly and tap sides of plate gently but firmly onto bench to get liquid to cover the bottom of every well. This is difficult, but these wells have a minimum recommended volume of 75ul, and the liquid really should cover the bottom of the well to ensure an accurate reading. You will need to tap harder than you think, but be careful! <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871252,"guid":"80D7F7903B9311EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","previous_id":871251,"previous_guid":"6CD793403B9311EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"83DA26C59E174A07901B447CD9C0BA98","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Plate Reader"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"AE4AC248EF6146C0B5604DD1FAFE4523","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>. <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Incubate for 2-5 minutes, keeping foil cover on to protect from light.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871253,"guid":"864D85003B9311EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","previous_id":871252,"previous_guid":"80D7F7903B9311EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"386155EB60684C9793C6FB5575E56AB2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Plate Reader"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BA92F6E0B0C54A5B913F21DB576DF900","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Read your samples on the plate reader, be sure to follow its specifications. Below is the settings used for the Willis lab:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Protocol settings for Willis_DNAquant50 protocol<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Plate layout: 96 well, read all of wells<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Excitation: 485 nm<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Emission: 530 nm<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Read from top<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Endpoint reading<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Detect fluorescence<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Sensitivity (= Gain): 50<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871255,"guid":"9E667ED03B9311EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","previous_id":871253,"previous_guid":"864D85003B9311EAA4046B1F57AE1FE9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1DCFA9A03F3E497CAFF515DC18F336DA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Calculating DNA concentrations"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B3440F6ADA8E43C5AD6C4C08DC1DC499","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Plot your standard curve DNA concentrations in ng\/ul (x) and fluorescence scores (y) as a scatter plot.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:center\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">y = mx + b<\/span><\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:center\"><\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">In Excel:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Select a data point. Go to Chart--> Add Trendline. The line should be linear, and check the \u201cdisplay equation on chart\u201d option, and the R<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">2<\/span><span> to make sure you didn\u2019t really mess up the standard curve, although that should be apparent from the line on the chart.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Solve for x to determine the concentration of your samples.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":null,"changed_on":1579531795}